						<div class="postbody">Okay, so if they are all separate DACs, are you suggesting that each DAC by itself is nonlinear to begin with? Or is there an additional nonlinearity resulting from how they are mixed together? (i.e. why does DMC affect triangle/noise, etc.)<br /><br />i.e. my model might look like:<br />apu0 = apu0_mix(s0_dac(s0),s1_dac(s1))<br />apu1 = apu1_mix(t_dac(t),n_dac(n),dmc_dac(dmc))<br /><br />I was wondering if the squares were digitally added, since the mixer formula adds them before doing anything else. ...not that I have any reason to trust the formula, I know it models some important characteristics of the hardware mix, but I don't have any empirical confirmation that it's correct yet (and it appears incorrect w.r.t. triangle in my very cursory initial tests).<br /><br />Since they're not, that kind of dashes my hopes that it might have been a little easier to model. I suppose I'm just going to have to try to measure all possible outputs, then try to create a model that fits it well enough.</div>

